In Python, all the functionalities related to the regular expressions are contained in the " re " module.

Examples - Sub function in re module

    >>> s.replace('road','rd')
    'white bright brd rd'
    
    >>> import re
    >>> re.sub('road$', 'rd',s)              # sub is used to replace and $ is used to indicate that we need to change only if it is the
    'white bright rd'                        # last word in the string
    

    >>> s = 'white rwhite bright broad'
    >>> re.sub('^white', 'wh', s)           # ^ is used to indicate that we need to change only of it is the first word in the string
    'wh rwhite bright broad'
